<H2><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C"><B>HYMN FOR LAUDS OF ADVENT FROM 17 DECEMBER</B></FONT></H2>
<H3><PRE>
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    Am                  G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A.  The voices of the prophets
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    announce the coming of the Lord
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                       G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    who brings to all men 
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                     Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    the gift of his peace.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C.  Behold a new light 
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    rises in the morning,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    a voice resounds:
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    the king of glory comes.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A.  At his first coming 
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    Christ came to save us,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    to heal our wounds
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    of body and spirit.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C.  At the end of time
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    he will return as Judge;
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    he will give the promised kingdom
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    to his faithful servants.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A.  Today, on our path
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    his light shines for us;
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    Jesus, the sun of grace,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    calls us to new life.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C.  It is you, O Christ, we seek;
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    it is you we want to know,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    to praise you forever
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    in your eternal kingdom.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A.  To you be praise, O Lord,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    born of the Virgin Mary,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    to the Father and the Holy Spirit
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                Am     G Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    for ever and ever. Amen.
</PRE></H3>
